headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. and Nikola Jokic each scored 30 points, and the Denver Nuggets held off the Charlotte Hornets 117-112 on Tuesday night to snap a two-game slide.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic, Nuggets hold off Hornets 117-112 to snap 2-game slide

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns scored 28 points and Anthony Edwards added 22 as the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the undermanned Detroit Pistons 119-100 on Tuesday night in a game with significant lottery implications.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Edwards lead Timberwolves past undermanned Pistons

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 24 points and the Miami Heat clinched a playoff spot and locked the Boston Celtics into the play-in tournament Tuesday night with a 129-121 victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat clinch playoff spot with 129-121 victory over Celtics

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 20 points, Paul George added 16 and the Los Angeles Clippers led all the way Tuesday night in a 115-96 win over the Toronto Raptors.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers lead all the way in 115-96 win over Raptors

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had his ninth triple-double of the season and Caris LeVert added 24 points to help Indiana rally past Philadelphia 103-94 on Tuesday night, ending the 76ers' eight-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers rally late for 103-94 win to snap 76ers streak,

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant had 21 points and eight assists, and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Chicago Bulls 115-107 on Tuesday night despite Zach LaVine’s 41 points.
— Ja Morant had 24 points, eight assists and seven rebounds as the Memphis Grizzlies used a third-quarter burst to beat the Dallas Mavericks 133-104 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Brooks help Memphis to 133-104 rout of Mavericks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 27 points and the Milwaukee Bucks kept up their chase of the No. 2 seed in the Eastern Conference with a 114-102 victory over the Orlando Magic on Tuesday night.

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole hit a go-ahead 3-pointer with 1:43 left, Andrew Wiggins scored the next time down and finished with 38 points, rallying the Golden State Warriors past the Phoenix Suns 122-116 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors rally for second straight night, beat Suns 122-116

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Terence Davis matched his season high with 27 points, Buddy Hield had 21 and the Sacramento Kings beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 122-106 on Tuesday night to keep their slim playoff hopes alive.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings complete sweep of Thunder, still hope for playoffs

events.name: New York Knicks at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Talen Horton-Tucker made the go-ahead 3-pointer with 21.1 seconds remaining in overtime, and the Los Angeles Lakers improved their hopes of avoiding the play-in tournament and prevented the New York Knicks from clinching a postseason berth with a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Horton-Tucker comes up big in OT as Lakers edge Knicks
